[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman, 75, hit by car in life-threatening condition

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 75-year-old woman who was hit by a car in Greater Manchester is in life-threatening condition, police say.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The woman was struck by a green Toyota Hilux shortly after 21:30 GMT on Friday on Manchester New Road in Middleton.
Police said they earlier tried to stop a car reportedly being driven erratically in Blackley, but the vehicle continued on towards Middleton.
A man, 39, was arrested at the scene of the crash on suspicion of dangerous driving and drink-driving.
He remains in custody for questioning.
Pc Ed Lister appealed for witness who saw a car travelling erratically on Victoria Avenue East to contact police.
